results.notes:
Growing in hundreds on a small lawn, an island within the paved area in front of Loop D restrooms. Caps up to 1.5 cm across. Odor of raw potatoes (confirmed by two people). The yellow suggested by the name can be seen only with a bit of imagination.

Basidia 4-spored, one measured 23+3 x 7. Spores 7-8 × 4-4.5. A few measured cheilocystidia were in the range 36-40 × 19-24. Hyphae of the pileipellis thick (up to 15 microns), which is characteristic of the species. Hyphae of the stipitipellis about 5.5 mircons wide.

M. flavescens is a European species, and we have here a perfect match with the description in http://www.mycena.no/flavescens.htm.

results.notes:
Fongarium: cKc0584
Date: 05.X.2016
Biotopes: pousse sur une souche pourrie de Fagus ;

Macromorphologie
Chapeau conique à campanulé lorsque jeune, étalé à plan-convexe à maturité, dont la marge est arrondie ou fibrilleuse, centre rarement subombonné, légèrement hygrophane, brun-rouge brun jaunâtre à l’état humide, à marge ocre jaunâtre, légèrement opalescente, sec à sordide ocre-jaune, naturellement fibrilleux, lorsqu’elles sont fraîches avec restes fibrilleux vélaires distincte, en particulier à la marge. 20-75 mm ;
Lames modérément bondé, adnées-échancré à étroitement adnées, segmentiforme à subventrues, gris pâle à gris-jaune puis gris olivâtre, avec reflet violacée, avec arête lamellaire finement fimbriées, concolores ou légèrement plus pâle ;
Pied cylindrique, souvent se rétrécissant vers la base, jaune pâle à l’apex, plus sombre en dessous, vers la base rouge-brun, avec zone annuliforme apprimées, fibrilleux, finement fibrilleux-subsquamuleuse longitudinalement, en particulier dans la partie inférieure ;
Chair crème, épaisse et ferme ;
Odeur indistincte ;
Saveur douce, légèrement amarescente :
Sporée violacé brun foncé ;

Monographie:
- Noordeloos, Machiel E. Strophariaceae s.l., Fungi Europaei Edizioni Candusso, N° 13, 2011, 648 p.

Confirmé par Claude Kaufholtz-Couture

Thallus continuous, areloate with narrow spaces between individual areoles, effigurate, brownish grey, prothallus partially present, usually darkened. Areoles often mottled grey-brown, with lighter areas usually toward edge and darker in center. Thallus K+R, hardly visible at 20x but at 100x very distinct and showing lots of norstictic acid crystals (see photos). Apothecia immersed, thaline margin not much raised, but disk often concave giving a raised appearance to the rim. Rim concolorous with thallus, disk black, lightly pruinose. Hymenium and hypothecium hyaline, epihymenium dark with green tinge, K+brown. Paraphyses moniliform. Pycnidia uncommon. Conidia average 15.5×1.2µm.

Spores 8/ascus, hyaline, globose, with a large oil drop and visible perispore. Average measurement 22.4×14.7µm (n=8).

Lots of Lichenostigma saxicola as a parasitic fungi on the thallus.

Habitat: Steep mountain slope, southwest aspect, mixed forest, Fagus sylvatica, Picea abies dominant, with scattered Larix decidua trees; in shade, partly protected from direct rain by tree canopies; calcareous, skeletal ground; under thicket of young Picea abies and about 3-4 m from a large Larix decidua tree, however not directly under its canopy; average precipitations ~ 3.000 mm/year, average temperature 4-6 deg C, elevation 860 m (2.820 feet), alpine phytogeographical region.

Substratum: soil.

Place: Zadnja Trenta valley, next to the trail leading southeast from No. 48. switchback of alpine Vršič pass road (Kugy’s monument), before the trail passes Milnarica gorge, East Julian Alps, Posočje, Slovenia EC.

Comments: This small but beautiful, orange-yellow bolete is widespread but in most regions a rare find. In Slovenia it was once protected and put on Red List. However, it is not listed in our last official document related to fungi protection from 2011. The reason is not known to me. This find is to my knowledge the second known one in the Upper Soča river region.

Growing solitary. Relatively young fruit-body. Pileus diameter 4 cm, sticky surface; stipe 4.8 cm long, max diameter 15 mm, firm, not hollow; flesh firm, not bruising, after a day in the refrigerator slightly bluing; smell almost none; taste mild, mushroomy, pleasant; SP abundant, golden-yellow, oac852.

Protected according to: Uredba o varstvu samoniklih gliv Uradni list RS, št. 57/1998, z dne 14. 8. 1998 (Regulation of protected wild growing fungi, Official Gazette of Republic Slovenia, no. 57/1998). Priloga 1. Red list, marked by R, denoting a rare species.
